---
/**
 * /desktop-only — the one page mobile / tablet user agents can reach.
 *
 * Alice's measurement instrument (keystroke timing, hold/flight intervals,
 * pause architecture) depends on a physical keyboard and timing precision
 * that mobile and tablet browsers cannot reliably provide. Rather than
 * silently degrade signal quality on a phone, we block.
 *
 * Two layers detect mobile:
 *   1. `src/middleware.ts` — server-side User-Agent regex catches phones,
 *      most Android tablets, and traditional iPad UAs. Redirects every
 *      non-static path here.
 *   2. Inline JS on every page (here intentionally absent — the loop guard
 *      lives in the snippet itself, but skipping it on the destination is
 *      cheaper) — catches iPad pretending to be Mac Safari (iPadOS 13+
 *      default), which the server-side regex cannot distinguish from a
 *      real Mac.
 *
 * Public surface — listed in `PUBLIC_PATHS` so middleware does not gate it.
 * Theme is locked light (no localStorage read).
 */
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Alice — laptop only</title>
    <style is:global>
      @import url('/fonts/styFonts.css');

      :root {
        --bg: #f5f2ed;
        --text: #1a1a1a;
        --text-muted: #6b6560;
        --border: #ccc5bc;
        --accent: #7a5a44;
      }

      * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

      body {
        font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }

      .desktop-only-wrap {
        max-width: 520px;
        text-align: center;
      }

      h1 {
        font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin: 0.7rem 0;
      }

      p strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="desktop-only-wrap">
      <h1>Alice is laptop only</h1>
      <p>
        The instrument measures keystroke timing, pauses, and revision
        patterns in ways that mobile and tablet browsers cannot reliably
        support. Open this page on a <strong>laptop or desktop browser</strong>
        to continue.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you reached this page on what you believe is a laptop, your
        browser may be advertising itself as mobile. Try a different
        browser, or contact the operator.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
